result.execSummary:
The defendant Jessica A Saunders was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Retail Theft - Intentionally Take >$500 - $5000) [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(b).
  • Retail Theft - Intentionally Take (<=$500) [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Jessica A Saunders in court, in custody, with attorney Katie Bricco for Kelsey Morin.    District Attorney's Office Law Intern, Konrad Paczuski, appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Counts 1 and 2.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Counts 3, 4 and 5 dismissed and read in.  Cases 15CF654, 15CM965, 15CM968, 15CM1008, and 15CM1012 dismissed and read in to this matter.

Court orders the following:

Count 1:
- Total sentence: 3 years 6 months (Initial Confinement: 1 year 6 months, Extended Supervision: 2 years) STAYED.  Credit for 6 days if revoked.
- Defendant IS eligible for Challenge Incarceration
- Defendant IS eligible for Substance Abuse Program
- 2 years Probation. 
- Court costs of $278.00 to be paid as a Condition of Probation
- Restitution in the amount of $2,950.48 to be paid (jointly and severally liable) as a Condition of Probation as follows:  $253.80 to Walmart; $2,696.68 to Pick N Save.
- DNA Surcharge of $250.00 to be paid as a Condition of Probation
- Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
- Conditions of Probation:  Maintain absolute sobriety/Random UAs.  No use or possession of alcohol/drug paraphernalia/drugs without a valid prescription.  Follow through with AODA treatment/counseling.  No contact with Pick N Save.  No contact with Brenda M.  
CONDITION TIME: 90 days - NON WORKING HOURS WITH STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS - STAYED for use by Agent.

Count 2:
- 45 days jail.  Credit for 45 days.  COURT DEEMS TIME SERVED.
- Court costs waived
- DNA Surcharge waived
- DNA Sample waived
